FBIS3-2770 "drchi049_a_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 March 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Russia's Yeltsin Orders `Retargeting' of Missiles OW1203175794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1530 GMT 12 Mar 94 OW1203175794 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, March 12 (XINHUA) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin ordered the Defense Ministry today to formulate measures for retargeting Russian strategic nuclear missiles away from the United States and Britain. The order was given to implement the Moscow agreement signed by the Russian and U.S. presidents on January 14, and to implement the joint statement issued by Yeltsin and British Prime Minister John Major on February 15, the Presidential Press Office said. According to the two agreements, the two sides will retarget their nuclear missiles away from each other by May 30.
